Fixed bug in RestApiFilter - Essentially this bug has to do with our API not adhering to the CORS specification. When a cross-domain request is made using CORS, two actual requests are executed, first a pre-flight OPTIONS request and then whatever request you really want to execute (POST, GET, PUT, etc.) As per the specification this pre-flight OPTIONS request never includes user authentication credentials - it exists solely to determine if the domain making the request can execute the endpoint - essentially you are authenticating the domain rather than the user. Our API was erroneously throwing a 401 (authentication required) error in response to these OPTIONS pre-flight requests (since they don't include Basic Auth credentials). This has been fixed. See this Stack Overflow: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/15734031/why-does-the-preflight-options-request-of-an-authenticated-cors-request-work-in
Fixed bug in Python code generation
